criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Clinical diagnosis of type 2 diabetes.

          2. Aged 18-70;

          3. HbA1c ≥ 8.0%

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Pregnancy;

          2. Chronic kidney disease (CKD stage 5);

          3. Senile dementia patients;

          4. With malignant tumor;

          5. Moderate and severe anemia;

          6. Severe liver dysfunction;

          7. Hemolytic anemia, aplastic anemia, massive blood loss or transfusion, chronic malaria;

          8. In the recent one week, large doses of salicylate, erythropoietin, antiretroviral
             drugs, ribavirin and other drugs that have an impact on the detection of glycosylated
             hemoglobin were used
